"OpenSSL, и директории для сертификатов. Файл ключей должен хранится в "
"директории, указанной здесь. В противном случае OpenSSL не будет их "
"использовать."

#. type: Content of: <section><para>
#: en/content/administration/email/smime.xml:235
msgid ""
"The next step is performed in the <link linkend=\"adminarea-smime\">S/MIME "
"configuration on the OTRS Admin page</link>. Here, you can import the "
"private key(s) of the OTRS system and the public keys of other communication "
"partners. Enter the public key that has been created in the beginning of "
"this section and added to OTRS."
msgstr ""
"Следующим шагом, который следует выполнить - перейти по ссылке <link linkend="
"\"adminarea-smime\"> Настройка S/MIME в Панели Администрирования</link>. "
"Здесь можно импортировать закрытые ключи OTRS-системы и открытые ключи "
"других партнеров. Введите публичный ключ, который был создан и добавлен в "
"OTRS в начале этого раздела."

#. type: Content of: <section><para>
#: en/content/administration/email/smime.xml:239
msgid ""
"Obviously, all public S/MIME keys of communication partners can be imported "
"using the <link linkend=\"adminarea-customer-users\">customer user "
"administration tool</link> as well."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/administration/email/smime.xml:243
msgid "Fetch S/MIME Certificates from Customer User Backends"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/email/smime.xml:245
msgid ""
"It is possible to use a Customer User Backed (such as LDAP) as the source of "
"public S/MIME certificates. This certificates could be imported into the "
"system and be displayed in <link linkend=\"adminarea-smime\">S/MIME "
"configuration on the OTRS Admin page</link> and they can be used from OTRS "
"to send encrypted emails to the customers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/email/smime.xml:248
msgid "In order to enable this feature is needed to:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/email/smime.xml:252
msgid "Enable <literal>SMIME</literal> in SysConfig"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/email/smime.xml:253
msgid "Enable <literal>SMIME::FetchFromCustomer</literal> in SysConfig"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/email/smime.xml:256
msgid ""
"Configure a customer user backend to provide the attribute "
"<literal>UserSMIMECertificate</literal> with the customer user S/MIME "
"certificate (there is an example for LDAP customer user mapping in <filename>"
"$OTRS_HOME/Kernel/Config/Defaults.pm</filename>)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/email/smime.xml:262
msgid "This feature can be used in three different ways:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/email/smime.xml:268
msgid "Incoming Emails:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/email/smime.xml:271
msgid ""
"A dedicated Postmaster filter (<literal>PostMaster::PreFilterModule###000-"
"SMIMEFetchFromCustomer</literal> in SysConfig) will extract the email "
"address of each incoming email and will try to find the email address is the "
"list of customers. If found it will try get the S/MIME certificate from "
"customer user attributes. If a certificate is found it will try to import it "
"(unless it was already imported)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/email/smime.xml:276
msgid "Specific email address or all customers:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/email/smime.xml:279
msgid ""
"The console command <literal>Maint::SMIME::CustomerCertificate::Fetch</"
"literal> can be used to import the S/MIME certificate of one customer email "
"address as:"
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/administration/email/smime.xml:282
#, no-wrap
msgid "shell> perl /opt/otrs/bin/otrs.Console.pl Maint::SMIME::CustomerCertificate::Fetch --email customer@example.com\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/email/smime.xml:287
msgid ""
"In this case the console command will try to match the supplied email "
"address with one of the customer users. If found it will try add to the "
"system the S/MIME certificate found in customer user properties (if the "
"certificate is not already added)."
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/administration/email/smime.xml:291
#, no-wrap
msgid "shell> perl /opt/otrs/bin/otrs.Console.pl Maint::SMIME::CustomerCertificate::Fetch --add-all\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/email/smime.xml:290
msgid ""
"The same console command can be used to import the S/MIME certificates of "
"all customer users (limited to <literal>CustomerUserSearchListLimit</"
"literal> property from the customer user backend). This option is "
"discouraged specially for systems with a large number of customer users as "
"it might require too much time to execute and depending on the limit it "
"might be possible that not all customer certificates will be fetch. Execute "
"the console command in this mode as: <placeholder type=\"screen\" id=\"0\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/email/smime.xml:296
msgid ""
"For this option the console command will query the customer user backends to "
"get all possible customers and for each it will check if there is a S/MIME "
"certificate. If a certificate is found, it will try to add it to the system "
"(if the certificate is not already added)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/email/smime.xml:301
msgid "Renew existing certificates:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/email/smime.xml:304
msgid ""
"Another console command <literal>Maint::SMIME::CustomerCertificate::Renew</"
"literal> can be used to check for all existing certificates in the system. "
"This verifies that the existing certificates from customer users matches the "
"ones that are retrieved by the customer user properties. Any new certificate "
"in the customer user backend will be added into the system (no certificates "
"are deleted in this process)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/email/smime.xml:307
msgid ""
"This console command is executed once a day by the OTRS daemon automatically "
"with the task <literal>Daemon::SchedulerCronTaskManager::"
"Task###RenewCustomerSMIMECertificates</literal> (as seen in SysConfig), but "
"it can be also executed manually on demand as:"
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/administration/email/smime.xml:310
#, no-wrap
msgid "shell> perl /opt/otrs/bin/otrs.Console.pl Maint::SMIME::CustomerCertificate::Renew\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><title>
#: en/content/administration/date-time.xml:6
msgid "Date and Time Related Functions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/administration/date-time.xml:9
msgid "Setting up business hours, holidays and time zones"
msgstr "Настройка периода рабочего времени, празников и часовых поясов"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/date-time.xml:12
msgid ""
"Some functions in OTRS, like escalations and <link linkend=\"unlock-tickets"
"\">automatic unlocking of tickets</link>, depend on a proper configuration "
"of business hours, time zones and holidays. You can define these via the "
"<link linkend=\"sysconfig\">SysConfig interface</link>, in <link linkend="
"\"ConfigReference_Section_Core_Time\">Core::Time</link>.  You can also "
"specify different sets of business hours, holidays and time zones as "
"separate 'Calendars' in <link linkend="
"\"ConfigReference_Section_Core_Time_Calendar1\">Core::Time::Calendar1</link> "
"through <link linkend=\"ConfigReference_Section_Core_Time_Calendar9\">Core::"
"Time::Calendar9</link>. Calendars can be defined by <link linkend="
"\"adminarea-queue\">queue settings</link>, or on SLA levels. This means "
"that, for example, you can specify a calendar with 5 x 8 business hours for "
"your 'standard' SLA, but create a separate calendar with 7 x 24 support for "
"your 'gold' SLA; as well as set a calendar for your 'Support-USA' queue with "
"a different time window than your 'Support-Japan' queue. OTRS can handle up "
"to 99 different calendars."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><title>
#: en/content/administration/date-time.xml:17
msgid "Time zones"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/date-time.xml:20
msgid ""
"OTRS needs to know which time zone should be used to store date and time "
"related data in the database. You can set this in <link linkend="
"\"ConfigReference_Setting_OTRSTimeZone\">Core::Time:OTRSTimeZone</link>.  "
"The default is UTC and if you set up a new OTRS it is strongly recommended "
"to leave it at this. If you updated from an OTRS older than version 6, you "
"must ensure that <literal>OTRSTimeZone</literal> is being set to a time zone "
"that matches your previous setup. Otherwise new data will be stored with a "
"different time zone than your existing data.  Once you decided on a time "
"zone and data was stored (tickets, etc.), you shouldn't change the time zone "
"anymore because otherwise you would end up with data stored in different "
"time zones."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/date-time.xml:26
msgid ""
"You can set a default time zone for new agents and customer users via <link "
"linkend=\"ConfigReference_Setting_UserDefaultTimeZone\">Core::Time:"
"UserDefaultTimeZone</link>. This time zone will be used for all users that "
"don't have selected a time zone in their preferences."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><title>
#: en/content/administration/date-time.xml:32
msgid "Business Hours"
msgstr "Рабочее время"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/date-time.xml:35
msgid ""
"Set up the working hours for your system in SysConfig <link linkend="
"\"ConfigReference_Setting_TimeWorkingHours\">Core::Time:TimeWorkingHours</"
"link>, or for your specific calendar in the calendar's configuration. OTRS "
"can handle a granularity of one hour. Checking the marks in the boxes 8, 9, "
"10 ... 17 corresponds with business hours of 8:00 AM - 6:00 PM."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/date-time.xml:39
msgid ""
"Only during business hours can tickets escalate, notifications for escalated "
"and pending tickets be sent, and tickets be unlocked."
msgstr ""
"Заявки эскалируются, уведомления для эскалированных и ожидающих заявок "
"отправляются и заявки разблокируются только в рабочее время."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><title>
#: en/content/administration/date-time.xml:45
msgid "Fixed Date Holidays"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/date-time.xml:48
msgid ""
"Holidays that are on a fixed date every year, such as New Year's Day or the "
"Fourth of July, can be specified in <link linkend="
"\"ConfigReference_Setting_TimeVacationDays\">TimeVacationDays</link>, or in "
"the corresponding section for the calendars 1-9."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/date-time.xml:52
msgid ""
"Tickets will not escalate nor get unlocked on dates defined in "
"TimeVacationDays."
msgstr ""
"Заявки не будт эскалироваться, ни разблокироваться в сроки, определенные как "
"\"Специально зарезервированные дни\"."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><note><para>
#: en/content/administration/date-time.xml:57
msgid ""
"By default, OTRS ships with the <emphasis>German</emphasis> holidays "
"installed."
msgstr "По умолчанию, OTRS работает по <emphasis>Немецким</emphasis> выходным."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><title>
#: en/content/administration/date-time.xml:64
msgid "Floating Holidays"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/date-time.xml:67
msgid ""
"Holidays such as Easter that do not have a yearly fixed date but instead "
"vary each year, can be specified in <link linkend="
"\"ConfigReference_Setting_TimeVacationDaysOneTime\">TimeVacationDaysOneTime</"
"link>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/date-time.xml:71
msgid ""
"Tickets will not escalate and will not be unlocked on dates defined in "
"TimeVacationDaysOneTime."
msgstr ""
"Заявки не будут эскалироваться и не будут разблокироваться в период времени "
"определенный как TimeVacationDaysOneTime."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><note><para>
#: en/content/administration/date-time.xml:76
msgid ""
"OTRS does not ship with any One-Time holidays pre-installed. This means that "
"you need to add holidays, such as Easter or Thanksgiving, to the system when "
"configuring OTRS."
msgstr ""
"OTRS поставляется без единого предустановленного One-Time-праздника. Это "
"означает, что во время настройки системы OTRS, нужно самостоятельно добавить "
"празники, такие как Пасха, День Благодарения."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/administration/date-time.xml:85
msgid "Automated Unlocking"
msgstr "Автоматические Разблокировки"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/date-time.xml:88
msgid ""
"Locked tickets can be automatically unlocked by the system. This feature "
"might be useful if, for example, an agent has locked tickets that need to be "
"processed, but he can't work on them for some reason, say because he is out "
"of the office on an emergency. The automated unlock feature unlocks tickets "
"after a given time to ensure that no locked tickets will be forgotten, "
"thereby allowing other agents to process them."
msgstr ""
"Заблокированные заявки могут быть разблокированы системой автоматически. Эта "
"опция может быть полезной, если, например, агент заблокировал заявки, "
"которые нужно обработать, но не работал с ними по определенной причине, "
"например был в отпуске. Чтобы убедится в том, что заблокированные заявки не "
"будут забыты и их обработают другие агенты, автоматическая разблокировка "
"разблокирует заблокированные заявки при истечении определенного времени."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/date-time.xml:92
msgid ""
"The amount of time before a ticket is unlocked can be specified in the <link "
"linkend=\"adminarea-queue\">queue settings</link> for every queue. The "
"command <filename>bin/otrs.Console.pl Maint::Ticket::Unlock</filename>, "
"which is executed periodically as a cron job, performs the automated "
"unlocking of tickets."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/date-time.xml:96
msgid ""
"Notifications on unlocked tickets are sent out only to those agents that "
"have the queue with the unlocked tickets set in \"My queues\", and that have "
"activated the notification on unlocked tickets in their personal <link "
"linkend=\"user-preferences\">preferences</link>."
msgstr ""
"Уведомления о разблокированных заявках отсылаются только тем агентам, "
"которые добавили очередь с разблокированными заявками в \"Мои очереди\", и "
"активировали в своих <link linkend=\"user-preferences\">настройках</link> "
"функцию уведомлений о разблокированных заявоках."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/date-time.xml:100
msgid "Tickets will be unlocked if all of the following conditions are met:"
msgstr ""
"Заявки будут заблокированы в том случае, если выполнятся следующие условия:"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/date-time.xml:106
msgid ""
"There is an <emphasis>unlock timeout</emphasis> defined for the queue the "
"ticket is in."
msgstr ""
"Для очереди в которой хранится заявка определяется <emphasis>время "
"разблокировки</emphasis> ."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/date-time.xml:111
msgid "The ticket is set to <emphasis>locked</emphasis>."
msgstr "Заявке присвоен статус <emphasis>заблокирована</emphasis>."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/date-time.xml:116
msgid "The ticket state is <emphasis>open</emphasis>."
msgstr "Заявке присвоен статус <emphasis>открыатая</emphasis>."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/date-time.xml:122
msgid ""
"The unlock timer will be reset if an agent adds a new external article to "
"the ticket. It can be of any of the following types: <emphasis>email-"
"external</emphasis>, <emphasis>phone</emphasis>, <emphasis>fax</emphasis>, "
"<emphasis>sms</emphasis>, or <emphasis>note-external</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"Если агент добавляет в заявку новую статью - таймер разблокировки будет "
"сброшен. Он может быть любым из следующих типов: <emphasis>внешний-email</"
"emphasis>, <emphasis>телефон</emphasis>, <emphasis>факс</emphasis>, "
"<emphasis>смс</emphasis>, или <emphasis>внешнее примечание</emphasis>."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/date-time.xml:126
msgid ""
"Also, if the last article in the ticket is created by an agent, and a "
"customer adds another one, either via web or email response, the unlock "
"timer will be reset."
msgstr ""
"Кроме этого, если последняя статья в заявке создана агентом, и клиент "
"добавляет еще одну, либо через веб-интерфейс либо по электронной почте, "
"таймер разблокировки также будет сброшен."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/date-time.xml:130
msgid ""
"The last event that will reset the unlock timer is when the ticket is "
"assigned to another agent."
msgstr ""
"Последнее событие, которое будет сбрасывать таймер разблокировки, когда "
"заявка передается другому агенту."

#. type: Content of: <section><title>
#: en/content/administration/pdf-output.xml:4
msgid "Customizing the PDF Output"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><para>
#: en/content/administration/pdf-output.xml:7
msgid "This section handles the configurable options for PDF output in OTRS."
msgstr ""
"В этом разделе приводится настройка опций для экспорта данных из OTRS в PDF."

#. type: Content of: <section><para>
#: en/content/administration/pdf-output.xml:11
msgid ""
"If you use the Print action from anywhere within the OTRS interface, it will "
"generate a formatted PDF file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><para>
#: en/content/administration/pdf-output.xml:14
msgid ""
"You can adjust the look of the files generated by OTRS by creating your own "
"logo and adding it to <link linkend=\"ConfigReference_Setting_PDF::LogoFile"
"\">PDF::LogoFile</link>. You can use <link linkend="
"\"ConfigReference_Setting_PDF::PageSize\">PDF::PageSize</link> to define the "
"standard page size of the generated PDF file (DIN-A4 or Letter), and also "
"<link linkend=\"ConfigReference_Setting_PDF::MaxPages\">PDF::MaxPage</link> "
"to specify the maximum number of pages for a PDF file, which is useful if a "
"user generates a huge output file by mistake."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><title>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface.xml:5
msgid "Generic Interface"
msgstr "Generic Interface"

#. type: Content of: <section><para>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface.xml:7
msgid ""
"The OTRS Generic Interface consists of a multiple layer framework that lets "
"OTRS communicate with other systems via a web service. This communication "
"could be bi-directional:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface.xml:13
msgid ""
"<emphasis>OTRS as Provider: </emphasis> OTRS acts as a server listening to "
"requests from the External System, processing the information, performing "
"the requested action, and answering the request."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>OTRS как Provider: </emphasis> OTRS заставляет сервер отслеживать "
"запросы от внешней системы, обрабатывать информацию, выполняя запрошенное "
"действие, и отвечать на запрос."

#. type: Content of: <section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface.xml:20
msgid ""
"<emphasis>OTRS as Requester: </emphasis> OTRS acts as a client collecting "
"information, sending the request to the Remote System, and waiting for the "
"response."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>OTRS как Requester: </emphasis> OTRS работает как клиент, "
"собирающий информацию, посылая запрос к Внешней системе, и ожидает ответа."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface.xml:32
msgid ""
"A Web Service is a communication method between two systems, in our case "
"OTRS and a Remote System."
msgstr ""
"Веб-сервисы это метод взаимодействия между двумя системами, в нашем случае, "
"OTRS и удаленной системой/Remote System."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface.xml:36
msgid ""
"The heart of the Web Service is its configuration, where it is defined what "
"actions the web service can perform internally (Operation), what actions the "
"OTRS request can perform Remote System (Invokers), how data is converted "
"from one system to the other (Mapping), and over which protocol the "
"communication will take place (Transport)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface.xml:42
msgid ""
"The Generic Interface is the framework that makes it possible to create Web "
"Services for OTRS in a predefined way, using already made building blocks "
"that are independent from each other and interchangeable."
msgstr ""
"Generic Interface - это инструмент, который позволяет создавать Web-сервисы "
"для OTRS предопределенным образом, используя уже готовые блоки, которые "
"независимы друг от друга и взаимозаменяемы."

#. type: Content of: <section><title>
#: en/content/administration/ticket/priorities.xml:6
msgid "Ticket Priorities"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><para>
#: en/content/administration/ticket/priorities.xml:9
msgid ""
"OTRS comes with five default priority levels that can be modified via the "
"\"Priorities\" link on the Admin page. When creating a customized list of "
"priorities, please keep in mind that they are sorted alphabetically in the "
"priority selection box in the user interface. Also, OTRS orders tickets by "
"internal database IDs in the QueueView."
msgstr ""
"OTRS поставляется с пятью предустановлеными уровнями приоритетов, которые "
"можно изменить перейдя по ссылке \"Приоритеты\" на Панели Администрирования. "
"При создании настраиваемого списка приоритетов, пожалуйста помните, что они "
"сортируются в алфавитном порядке. Также OTRS сортирует заявки в QueueView по "
"их внутреннему номеру (ID)."

#. type: Content of: <section><note><para>
#: en/content/administration/ticket/priorities.xml:14
msgid ""
"As with other OTRS entities, priorities may not be deleted, only deactivated "
"by setting the Valid option to <emphasis>invalid</emphasis> or "
"<emphasis>invalid-temporarily</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"Как и в случае с другими сущностями OTRS, приоритеты не могут быть удалены, "
"а только деактивированы путем установки параметра Действительный в значение "
