#. type: Content of: <section><para>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface/genericinterface-webservice-configuration.xml:7
msgid ""
"From its design the web services were conceived to be portable from one OTRS "
"system to another, e.g. from a test or development environment to a "
"production system. Therefore it was needed to have an easy way to extract "
"the web service configuration from the database, and import it to another. "
"To accomplish this task the Generic Interface uses YAML files as the web "
"services configuration basis."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><para>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface/genericinterface-webservice-configuration.xml:14
msgid ""
"Why YAML? YAML is a markup language designed to be human friendly to read "
"and write (it is easier to understand than JSON), it does not have some of "
"the limitations of XML like numeric tags, it is open, standardized, and is "
"complete enough to store the whole web service configuration."
msgstr ""
"Почему YAML? YAML это язык разметки, разработанный специально "
"человекочитаемым и удобным для написания (он более понятен чем  JSON), не "
"имеет некоторых ограничений XML, таких как числовые тэги, он открыт, "
"стандартизован и полностью удовлетворяет задаче хранения всех настроек веб-"
"сервисов."

#. type: Content of: <section><note><para>
#: en/content/administration/genericinterface/genericinterface-webservice-configuration.xml:21
msgid ""
"To learn more about YAML please visit <ulink url=\"http://www.yaml.org/"
"\">http://www.yaml.org/</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Чтобы узнать больше о YAML пожалуйста посетите ссылку <ulink url=\"http://"
"www.yaml.org/\">http://www.yaml.org/</ulink>."

