#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/appointment-calendar/introduction.xml:57
msgid ""
"To have a good overview of available appointments within different calendars "
"and the related dates they start or end, it is possible to select different "
"view modes, like weekly view, monthly view, different timeline related views "
"etc."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/appointment-calendar/introduction.xml:62
msgid ""
"Within the agenda overview, an agent is able to display the appointments of "
"all available (accessible) calendars in a table-like overview. This overview "
"is designed to have a detailed list of upcoming appointments in a structured "
"table. Like in the calendar overview, appointments can be created, edited or "
"deleted. This view supports a monthly, weekly and daily point of view on "
"available appointments."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/appointment-calendar/introduction.xml:70
#: en/content/appointment-calendar/usage.xml:416
msgid "Repeating appointments"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/appointment-calendar/introduction.xml:72
msgid ""
"If recurring appointments needs to be archived, it is possible to setup "
"detailed information about the occurrences of a single appointment."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/appointment-calendar/introduction.xml:76
msgid ""
"Beside pre-defined frequencies like daily, weekly, monthly etc. it is "
"possible to setup custom repeats and exclude weekdays or dates of months, "
"define the amount of recurrences and/or the end date after the appointment "
"stops to repeat."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/appointment-calendar/introduction.xml:82
#: en/content/appointment-calendar/usage.xml:488
msgid "Notifications"
msgstr "Уведомления"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/appointment-calendar/introduction.xml:84
msgid ""
"Within the edit screen of an appointment, it is possible to setup a date to "
"notify about the appointment."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/appointment-calendar/introduction.xml:88
msgid ""
"As in the settings for appointment repeat, it is possible to use pre-defined "
"templates for notifications (i.e. 5 minutes before, 15 minutes before etc.) "
"or setup a custom point of time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/appointment-calendar/introduction.xml:93
msgid ""
"The custom settings for notifications allows to setup a relative point of "
"time (like 5 minutes after the appointment has been started) or an explicit "
"date/time expression."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/appointment-calendar/introduction.xml:99
#: en/content/appointment-calendar/usage.xml:518
msgid "Event-based appointment/calendar notifications"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/appointment-calendar/introduction.xml:101
msgid ""
"As in the well-known ticket notifications, this package comes up with an "
"event based notification mechanism, that can be handled using an "
"administration interface.  Within that interface, notification event entries "
"can be created, updated and/or deleted to react on different OTRS events "
"with related filters, recipients and content templates."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/appointment-calendar/introduction.xml:108
msgid ""
"The content of notifications can be dynamically filled-up using OTRS smart "
"tags, like in the event based ticket notifications."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/appointment-calendar/introduction.xml:113
#: en/content/appointment-calendar/usage.xml:817
msgid "Managed ticket appointments"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/appointment-calendar/introduction.xml:115
msgid ""
"This package offers the possibility to automatically create and update "
"appointments in calendars based on ticket data, using special rules defined "
"within the calendar edit screen. Any ticket date/time value (i.e. pending "
"time, escalation times or dynamic fields) can be used to define appointment "
"start and end dates."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/appointment-calendar/introduction.xml:122
#: en/content/appointment-calendar/usage.xml:749
msgid "Link tickets to appointments"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/appointment-calendar/introduction.xml:124
msgid ""
"Within the edit screen of an appointment, it is possible link existing "
"tickets."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/appointment-calendar/introduction.xml:127
msgid "Tickets can be searched by their ticket numbers and/or titles."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/appointment-calendar/introduction.xml:130
msgid ""
"Links between tickets and appointments appear in the ticket zoom like every "
"other linked objects in a related table."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/appointment-calendar/introduction.xml:134
msgid ""
"Those links can either be created through an existing appointment, using the "
"overviews or via the link feature in the ticket zoom."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/appointment-calendar/introduction.xml:138
msgid ""
"It's also possible to create a new appointment out of the ticket zoom, which "
"links the related ticket automatically to the new appointment."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/appointment-calendar/introduction.xml:143
#: en/content/appointment-calendar/usage.xml:1014
msgid "Dashboard widget for upcoming appointments"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/appointment-calendar/introduction.xml:145
msgid ""
"Every agent can activate a dashboard widget <emphasis>Appointments</"
"emphasis> in the dashboard."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/appointment-calendar/introduction.xml:149
msgid ""
"This widget shows the upcoming appointments of the different calendars for "
"today, tomorrow and the next 5 days."
