msgid "With this step, the basic system setup is finished."
msgstr "На этом, начальная установка системы закончена."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:349
msgid "Step 10: Start the OTRS Daemon"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:352
msgid ""
"The new OTRS daemon is responsible for handling any asynchronous and "
"recurring tasks in OTRS.  What has been in cron file definitions previously "
"is now handled by the OTRS daemon, which is now required to operate OTRS. "
"The daemon also handles all GenericAgent jobs and must be started from the "
"<literal>otrs</literal> user."
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:359
#, no-wrap
msgid "shell> /opt/otrs/bin/otrs.Daemon.pl start\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:366
msgid "Step 11: Cron jobs for the OTRS user"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:368
msgid ""
"There are two default OTRS cron files in <filename>/opt/otrs/var/cron/*."
"dist</filename>, and their purpose is to make sure that the OTRS Daemon is "
"running.  They need to be be activated by copying them without the \".dist\" "
"filename extension."
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:374
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"shell> cd /opt/otrs/var/cron\n"
"shell> for foo in *.dist; do cp $foo `basename $foo .dist`; done\n"
msgstr ""
"shell> cd /opt/otrs/var/cron\n"
"shell> for foo in *.dist; do cp $foo `basename $foo .dist`; done\n"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:381
msgid ""
"To schedule these cron jobs on your system, you can use the script "
"<filename>Cron.sh</filename> with the <literal>otrs</literal> user."
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:386
#, no-wrap
msgid "shell> /opt/otrs/bin/Cron.sh start\n"
msgstr "shell> /opt/otrs/bin/Cron.sh start\n"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:392
msgid "Stopping the cron jobs is also possible (useful for maintenance):"
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:396
#, no-wrap
msgid "shell> /opt/otrs/bin/Cron.sh stop\n"
msgstr "shell> /opt/otrs/bin/Cron.sh stop\n"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:403
msgid "Step 12: Setup bash autocompletion (optional)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:405
msgid ""
"All regular OTRS commandline operations happen via the otrs Console "
"interface <filename>bin/otrs.Console.pl</filename>. This provides an auto "
"completion for the bash shell which makes finding the right command and "
"options much easier."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:410
msgid ""
"You can activate the bash autocompletion by installing the package "
"<literal>bash-completion</literal>.  It will automatically detect and load "
"the file <filename>/opt/otrs/.bash_completion</filename> for the "
"<literal>otrs</literal> user."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:414
msgid ""
"After restarting your shell, you can just type <filename>bin/otrs.Console."
"pl</filename> followed by TAB, and it will list all available commands. If "
"you type a few characters of the command name, TAB will show all matching "
"commands. After typing a complete command, all possible options and "
"arguments will be shown by pressing TAB."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/source.xml:422
